As a result, travelers (especially those who have underlying health problems) may want to cancel or postpone upcoming vacation plans.
Amtrak is allowing customers with existing or new reservations made before April 30 to change the date of their travel without paying change fees.
AdvertisementWhere can I find health and travel updates regarding the coronavirus?
The Los Angeles Times’ Health: Coronavirus web page provides news about the outbreak in California and elsewhere, and tips about what you can do to avoid getting infected.
Also, the CDC’s Traveler’s Health website and the World Health Organization’s coronavirus disease information page provide solid information about what’s happening worldwide with the coronavirus oubreak.